description:
TL;DR - Severely over priced;

40 bucks for garlic noodles and 4 prawns; garlic noodles alone cost 11 dollars, so i paid 29 dollars for the prawns or 7 dollars for each. I cannot get over paying 40 dollars for a mediocre meal.  

Service was great and attentive. really empty for a week night.  Building looks like it isn't taken care of.

Was there on 17th March for late dinner.

The food was generally good:
- Roasted garlic crabs were good;
- Garlic noodles were good;
- I would skip the vegetables (very average).

Service was below average:
- Despite us having a reservation and it being late (9:30pm) and the restaurant not being full, the staff would not seat us until most everyone had arrived;
- Our server tried to pressure-sell us into ordering more crabs than we needed.  To illustrate this point, in the end we ordered 2/3 the amount she recommended and it was still too much.

If you like roasted garlic crab and garlic garlic noodles and can live with not-so-good service, then it may be worth a visit.

But if service bothers you and detracts from your overall experience, then this might not be the place for you.
